$\implies$ If then (Conditional)
$\iff$ If and only If

$\neg (p\lor \neg (q\lor \neg r))\equiv F$

$p\implies q$ 
means "I promise that, if p happens, q will happen."

Example:

Statement:
If Maria wins the lottery, she will distribute 1000 dollars

Situation:
Maria wins, distributes 1000, $T\implies T\equiv T$
Maria wins, keep all money,$T\implies F\equiv F$
Maria loses, distributes 1000, $F\implies T\equiv T$
Maria loses, keeps all money, $F\implies F\equiv T$

Example:

Statement: Oxygen is necessary for survival
Logical Statement: survival $\implies$ oxygen

Statement: You die when you are beheaded
Logical Statement: beheaded $\implies$ death

Three Statements related to p$\implies$q

Inverse $\neg p\implies \neg q$
Converse $q\implies p$
Contrapositive $\neg q \implies \neg p$

Inverse and converse are not equivalent to $p\implies q$
Contrapositive is equivalent to $p\implies q$


If and Only means that $p \iff q$ is true when p and q have the same truth value

$p \iff q\equiv (p\implies q)\land (q\implies p)$
